The pilot reported that, during landing, the airplane touched down and bounced. He aborted 
the landing, but the airplane did not climb although the engine was operating at full power. 
The airplane veered to the right and became momentarily airborne as it exited the runway. The 
airplane struck the ground hard and nosed over.
The airplane sustained substantial damage to both wings, the fuselage, and the empennage.
The METAR at the time of the accident reported that the wind was calm and that skies were 
clear. The temperature was 99Â°F, and the altimeter setting was 30.12 inches of mercury. 
